# No buffer SH1106 OLED display driver

## FEATURES
 * no buffer, but does pixel-by-pixel update
 * slower than the buffered libs
 * basic functionality
 * optimized for size
 * for small devices with minimal resources ([Atmel AVR ATtiny family](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atmel_AVR_ATtiny_comparison_chart))


## FUNCTIONS
### Draw a pixel
_fillme_

### Draw a filled rectangle
_fillme_

### Print text
_fillme_

### Display a bitmap
_fillme_

## GETTING STARTED
_fillme_
```c++
#include "SH1106Lib.h"
SH1106Lib display;

void setup() {
	display.initialize();
	display.clearDisplay();
}

void loop() {
 // use display.
}
```


## CONSIDERATIONS
 * Printing text do not span the page boundary (aka y % 8 == 0) lines are faster
 * Plotting individual pixels in large numbers is slow


